<p>I am developing Rest web service using Dropwizard .I need to return my response in vendor specific content type.say I have an API for getItemdetails. For that I have annotated my <code>enter code here</code> Item.java with</p>  <pre><code> @XmlRootElement  </code></pre>  <p>and have annotated the resource class ItemResource.java with</p>  <pre><code>@Component @Path("/item") @Produces("application/vnd.bks.pit.yit-v1.3+xml") </code></pre>  <p>Inside getItemdeatails :</p>  <pre><code>public Response  getItemdeatails( @Context Request request){  return Response.ok(item)                    .header(HttpHeaders.CONTENT_TYPE,new MediaType("application", "vnd.bks.pit.yit-v1.3+xml"))                    .build(); </code></pre>  <p>This is working .But not sure if it is correct way to achieve the same.</p>  <p>1)Is there a way by which I can directly return Item instead of response with vendor specific content type or Response is fine</p>  <p>2) My response XML has tag like </p>  <pre><code> &lt;item:item-details-response xmlns:item="http://bks.com/pit/yit/item-details-response/" version="1.3"&gt;      &lt;product-name&gt;Shirt&lt;/product-name&gt;      &lt;product-price&gt;15.99&lt;/product-price&gt;      &lt;product-description&gt; slim fit.&lt;/product-description&gt;  </code></pre>  <p>So how do I model my Item class so that it forms a response xml in this format ?how do i add the item:item-details-response with namespace to my response object. I am new to Rest and Dropwizard. Request someone to please help with this.</p>  <p>The other tags I could achieve using </p>  <pre><code>@XmlRootElement(name="item-details-response") @XmlAccessorType(XmlAccessType.FIELD) public class Item {     @XmlElement(name="product-name") private String name;     @XmlElement(name="product-description") private String description;     @XmlElement(name="product-price") private String price;    public String getName() {     return name; } public void setName(String name) {     this.name = name; }   public String getDescription() {     return description; }  public void setDescription(String description) {     this.description = description; }  public String getPrice() {     return price; } public void setPrice(String price) {     this.price = price; }   } </code></pre>  <p>I get the response as </p>  <p>Addded following in package-info.java  </p>  <pre><code>@XmlSchema(xmlns={         @XmlNs(             prefix="item",              namespaceURI="http://bks.com/pit/yit/item-details-response/") })     &lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?&gt;&lt;item-details-response xmlns:item="http://bks.com/pit/yit/item-details-response/"&gt;&lt;product-name&gt;Shirt&lt;/product-name&gt;&lt;product-description&gt;slim fit&lt;/product-description&gt;&lt;product-price&gt;1$&lt;/product-price&gt;&lt;/item-details-response&gt; </code></pre>  <p>How do I add the the namespace element to be item: for item-details-response tag in the response xml ?</p>